de.engehausen.treemap.impl

Class GenericTreeModel<N>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.engehausen.treemap.impl.GenericTreeModel<N>
  • Type Parameters:
    N - the type this model holds
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ITreeModel<N>, IWeightedTreeModel<N>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FileModel

    public class GenericTreeModel<N>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IWeightedTreeModel<N>
    Sample weighted tree model implementation. In addition to the weighted tree model interface this implementation allows adding nodes to the tree, which is of course needed to build the model.

      • add

        public void add(N node,
       long weight,
       N parent,
       boolean propagateWeights)
        Adds the given node to the parent and propagates the nodes' weight upwards to the root.
        Parameters:
        node - the node to add, must not be null.
        weight - the weight of the node
        parent - the parent of the node; if the parent is null the given node will be the root node of the model.
        propagateWeights - true to propagate the weight of the given node upwards to its parents, false otherwise.
